HEADWORD: Antiphrasis
<hw>An*tiph"ra*sis</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
Gr. <?/, fr. <?/ to express by antithesis or negation.]</ety>
<fld>(Rhet.)</fld> <def>The use of words in a sense opposite to their
proper meaning; as when a court of justice is called a <xex>court of
vengeance</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

